<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="19" pageNumber="260">
Notes. This species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Viraktamath 2004" authorityName="Viraktamath" authorityYear="2004" box="[628,967,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xenovarta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ankusha">
<emphasis box="[628,753,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="260">X. ankusha</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Viraktamath, C. A." box="[761,967,763,789]" pageId="19" pageNumber="260" pagination="1 - 47" refId="ref19746" refString="Viraktamath, C. A. (2004) A revision of the Varta - Stymphalus generic complex of the leafhopper tribe Scaphytopiini (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae) from the Old World. Zootaxa, 713 (1), 1 - 47. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 713.1.1" type="journal article" year="2004">Viraktamath 2004</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, described from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1262,1332,763,789]" name="China" pageId="19" pageNumber="260">China</collectingCountry>
, which it closely resembles in overall appearance including head shape, color pattern and in the structure of the subgenital plates. The new species differs in having the ventral margin of the pygofer lobe strongly emarginate preapically with a broad ventroapical lobe, and the aedeagus with the left process much larger, expanded medially and bladelike, and the distal process curved toward rather than away from the left process.
</paragraph>
